24:04.560 --> 24:09.600
Having had a decent night's
sleep, we convened to plan
our next move.

24:10.880 --> 24:12.200
-Morning.
-Hello.

24:12.280 --> 24:14.000
What's the matter
with your face?

24:14.080 --> 24:15.640
-Is it not good?
-No.

24:15.720 --> 24:17.480
It's like being in
The Singing Detective.

24:17.560 --> 24:19.160
-(LAUGHTER)
-It is.

24:19.240 --> 24:20.800
-That's bloody rude.
Anyway, listen...
-(HUMMING)

24:20.880 --> 24:22.520
Sorry, I'm briefly
mesmerised.

24:22.600 --> 24:23.680
-Listen.
RICHARD: I'm back.

24:23.760 --> 24:24.920
While you were out
this morning

24:25.000 --> 24:26.400
buying new action
trousers, I see,

24:26.480 --> 24:29.120
I have got a book...

24:29.200 --> 24:32.000
All of Colombia's wildlife
is in this book, yeah?

24:32.080 --> 24:33.560
All of it.

24:33.640 --> 24:35.640
I've been through it.

24:35.720 --> 24:38.560
-Guess what there isn't?
-A hippopotamus.

24:38.640 --> 24:41.200
Well, so far we've
got pigeon, dog, horse...

24:41.280 --> 24:43.200
Donkey.

24:43.280 --> 24:44.720
Don't bring those up, please.

24:44.800 --> 24:46.520
-Um, jaguar.
RICHARD: Jaguar.

24:46.600 --> 24:48.040
-Bear.
JEREMY: Bear.
RICHARD: Yes.

24:48.120 --> 24:51.440
Condor is next.
Condor is next.

24:51.520 --> 24:54.320
Is there a case...
I think there is.

24:54.400 --> 24:56.320
...for a little light
car modification?

24:56.400 --> 24:57.960
RICHARD:
I agree, there is, there is.

24:58.040 --> 24:59.960
I think I might be
scaring them off a bit.

25:00.040 --> 25:02.000
-I could make some changes.
-I'm just thinking...

25:02.080 --> 25:03.600
Tell you what
I could give my car...

25:03.680 --> 25:06.520
-A roof.
-Yeah, that's a good idea.

25:06.600 --> 25:08.400
There is evidence to suggest
in your flaking visage...

25:08.480 --> 25:11.560
Then you wouldn't look like
Michael Gambon in the '80s.

25:11.640 --> 25:13.840
I am Michael Gambon
in the '80s.

25:13.920 --> 25:15.920
â™ª LOS YETIS:
Llegaron Los Peluqueros

25:18.560 --> 25:22.560
JEREMY: We then went
shopping in Bogota's
massive auto district.

25:22.640 --> 25:27.400
20 city blocks of nothing
but shops selling car parts.

25:33.720 --> 25:37.520
All I really need,
if I'm honest,
to make my car better,

25:37.600 --> 25:39.760
is some kind of ladder,

25:39.840 --> 25:43.680
so I get some elevation
for the photography,

25:43.760 --> 25:46.760
and a chair to sit on,
and a roof.

25:48.800 --> 25:50.720
RICHARD: Oh, gold dust.

25:50.800 --> 25:52.440
Look at that.

25:52.520 --> 25:54.520
That is perfect.

25:54.600 --> 25:59.320
So, um, can I have 20 metres?

25:59.400 --> 26:01.400
Vingt me...?

26:03.240 --> 26:05.200
That's not a good sign,
is it?

26:05.280 --> 26:08.960
(MUSICAL BLAST FROM HORN)

26:09.040 --> 26:14.040
JEREMY: As we went about
our shopping, I received a
rather intriguing phone call.

26:15.840 --> 26:17.800
This afternoon?

26:17.880 --> 26:19.960
Sure. OK.

26:20.040 --> 26:21.440
All right, bye.

26:21.520 --> 26:23.160
Er, that was
our Colombian fixers.

26:23.240 --> 26:25.840
They say, um, this afternoon
they want us to try something

26:25.920 --> 26:30.480
which is, they say...
the thing that Colombia
is most famous for.

26:34.160 --> 26:36.000
Yep.

26:36.080 --> 26:37.880
Football.

26:37.960 --> 26:42.800
Specifically a match
between The Grand Tour
team...

26:42.880 --> 26:45.320
and our Colombian fixers.

26:45.400 --> 26:50.280
Hammond, with his gammy knee,
couldn't play, so made
himself our manager.

26:50.360 --> 26:56.160
So, we're gonna play
a five-four-four?

26:56.240 --> 26:57.880
JEREMY: I doubt it.
-Five-four-three?

26:57.960 --> 26:59.320
MAN: Eight, nine?
-Five... Two?

26:59.400 --> 27:01.200
-How many on our team?
-It's eight a side.

27:01.280 --> 27:02.880
Three. Right, well,
we're gonna play...

27:02.960 --> 27:07.360
-Drop the five, then.
-Three... four.

27:07.440 --> 27:09.440
Three.

27:09.520 --> 27:11.160
JEREMY: With the crowd
of onlookers

27:11.240 --> 27:15.320
at fever pitch,
the game began.

27:15.400 --> 27:17.880
(WHISTLE)

27:17.960 --> 27:23.840
And since I was our biggest
player, from any angle,
I was put in goal.

27:23.920 --> 27:25.920
Which went well.

27:35.000 --> 27:38.040
Also,
the ref was pretty harsh.

27:38.120 --> 27:40.280
-(WHISTLE)
-What?

27:40.360 --> 27:41.800
How can it be handball?

27:41.880 --> 27:44.720
He hasn't got a hand!

27:44.800 --> 27:46.400
-(WHISTLE)
-The match continued

27:46.480 --> 27:49.080
with some good clean tackles
from us.

27:50.480 --> 27:52.760
(WHISTLE)

27:52.840 --> 27:55.280
And eventually
an actual goal.

27:57.520 --> 27:58.680
-(CHEERING)
-(WHISTLE)

27:58.760 --> 28:02.960
But my goalkeeping continued
to let the side down.

28:03.040 --> 28:05.040
-Oh, come on!
-(WHISTLE)

28:06.480 --> 28:08.680
-(WHISTLE)
-(CLAPPING)

28:08.760 --> 28:11.320
And even though
I'd given my all...

28:11.400 --> 28:14.280
(COUGHS) I've just coughed
my lungs up.

28:14.360 --> 28:18.600
I was eventually substituted
for our special forces
security guy,

28:18.680 --> 28:23.360
who did well,
despite his pixelated face.

28:23.440 --> 28:27.080
(CHEERING)

28:27.160 --> 28:30.760
-We may as well modify our
cars now. We're not playing.
-Yeah.

28:30.840 --> 28:33.840
The only problem is,
nobody'll be able to film us.

28:33.920 --> 28:36.640
Cos they're playing football.
And they are not stopping.

28:36.720 --> 28:38.800
Why don't we just quietly
leave them to it?

28:38.880 --> 28:42.240
-We'll get on with it.
JAMES: It's not as if
anyone's gonna miss us.

28:43.480 --> 28:45.920
(GRUNTING)

28:47.040 --> 28:49.040
-Go on, Nick!
-(WHISTLE)

28:56.320 --> 28:58.080
JEREMY:
The next morning, happily,

28:58.160 --> 29:01.960
the uninjured members of our
film crew were back at work.

29:03.320 --> 29:06.680
-Was it really six-two?
-Yeah.

29:06.760 --> 29:08.640
-It was.
-Yeah.

29:08.720 --> 29:11.280
I think the problem was
they substituted me and you
too early.

29:11.360 --> 29:13.520
-I think so.
-Anyway, listen...

29:13.600 --> 29:15.440
We've now got
the film crews back,

29:15.520 --> 29:17.760
so let's set them to work
doing what they can do,

29:17.840 --> 29:19.640
and have a look at our cars.

29:19.720 --> 29:21.840
-OK, you have to find mine.
-Where is it?

29:21.920 --> 29:24.320
Yours is the one disguised
as a bush
in an industrial car park.

29:24.400 --> 29:26.800
-I've camouflaged it.
-Well, yes,
you've painted it.

29:26.880 --> 29:30.040
It's got roll-down netting
that goes over the windows
when I'm using it as a hide

29:30.120 --> 29:33.080
and it has an inbuilt...
Well, it's got a raise
on it as well,

29:33.160 --> 29:35.760
cos the one problem
I've had is ground clearance.

29:35.840 --> 29:37.240
-Yeah.
-What?

29:37.320 --> 29:39.120
You've spent two days
laughing at Hammond and me

29:39.200 --> 29:41.080
cos we've got cars
that have been raised,

29:41.160 --> 29:43.880
and how awful they are,
and then you've done
exactly the same.

29:43.960 --> 29:47.600
As an alternative expression,
rather than
"I'm going to raise my car,"

29:47.680 --> 29:50.560
-why not, "I'm going to
ruin my car"?
-Yes.

29:50.640 --> 29:52.120
-What you've done
is ruined it.
-Let's see.

29:52.200 --> 29:53.840
I've done it very subtly.

29:53.920 --> 29:56.720
How do you think Tony Blair
and Gordon Sting
are going to feel

29:56.800 --> 30:00.440
when they see that
you've turned their Panda
into a monster Panda?

30:00.520 --> 30:03.360
Very happy, actually.
That's communist camouflage.

30:03.440 --> 30:05.640
I got it from a picture
of a Russian tank.

30:05.720 --> 30:08.200
This is my idea.
PA system. I always do this.

30:08.280 --> 30:09.720
-It's not a PA system.
-Well, it is.

30:09.800 --> 30:12.920
It's a bird call
and animal call system.

30:13.000 --> 30:15.200
I have an iPad,
other tablets are available,
in the car

30:15.280 --> 30:17.120
in which I can select a
number of animal noises

30:17.200 --> 30:19.560
and they play out
of those speakers.
It's a lure.

30:19.640 --> 30:21.960
Well, can we move on
to Hammond,
who's obviously gone...

30:22.040 --> 30:23.960
-If you can find it.
-...completely mad.

30:24.040 --> 30:26.360
(RICHARD CLEARS HIS THROAT)
I too have gone the
camouflage route

30:26.440 --> 30:28.760
because it's green,
as you can see.

30:28.840 --> 30:30.560
I've mended the half shaft
up here.

30:30.640 --> 30:32.320
That's the only mechanical
work I've had to do

30:32.400 --> 30:34.640
because other than that
it's been perfect.

30:34.720 --> 30:38.080
Yes, this structure here
is a hide.

30:38.160 --> 30:41.880
I know it is. It's a hide
on a monster truck.

30:41.960 --> 30:45.480
It's people that they're
scared of and they won't
see any people.

30:45.560 --> 30:47.920
Those all drop down
and in there
I've got everything I need

30:48.000 --> 30:50.520
because often you're
sitting and waiting a long
time to take pictures.

30:50.600 --> 30:53.520
We've learnt that.
I can cook, eat,
entertain myself

30:53.600 --> 30:57.400
whilst waiting to capture
an award-winning photograph
of an animal.

30:57.480 --> 31:00.120
And this rotates
through 360 degrees.

31:00.200 --> 31:02.000
-I see.
-And you, because it's you,

31:02.080 --> 31:05.040
you put two cameras in there
to film yourself.

31:05.120 --> 31:07.520
Yes, that's the most
important thing.

31:07.600 --> 31:11.160
I love the idea that you two,
I'm afraid there's no other
word, morons,

31:11.240 --> 31:13.760
have decided that somehow
you can camouflage your car

31:13.840 --> 31:16.000
so they won't be seen
by animals.

31:16.080 --> 31:20.760
I have already proved that
mine can drive right up to
a bear, he's interested.

31:20.840 --> 31:22.520
Speaking of yours,
what have you done?

31:24.040 --> 31:26.440
Whoa, what's all that
on the back?

31:26.520 --> 31:28.400
That, gentlemen,
is a scissor lift.

31:28.480 --> 31:30.040
-What?
-It's a scissor lift.

31:30.120 --> 31:33.320
Simply get in that and rise
up, so then I have a...

31:33.400 --> 31:36.080
-Oh, so you're going to be
a window cleaner.
-(LAUGHS)

31:36.160 --> 31:40.800
The only thing this didn't
really have was proper
elevation. Now I have it.

31:40.880 --> 31:43.400
-How high does it go?
-38 feet.
-(RICHARD LAUGHS)

31:43.480 --> 31:45.440
-Really?
-Yes.
-It'll just fall over.

31:45.520 --> 31:47.400
A-ha, that's why I fitted it
with outriggers.

31:47.480 --> 31:48.920
They're not far enough apart.

31:49.000 --> 31:50.600
-Or big enough.
-They slide...

31:50.680 --> 31:51.960
How much does it weigh, that?

31:52.040 --> 31:54.640
-I've added half a tonne.
-(RICHARD LAUGHS)

31:54.720 --> 31:57.120
And there's something else
I've done.

31:57.200 --> 31:59.960
Oxygen is fitted
for my engine.

32:00.040 --> 32:02.240
-Why do you need oxygen?
-Because we're going
very high.

32:02.320 --> 32:04.440
-Well, 38 feet.
-No, 15,000 feet.

32:04.520 --> 32:06.840
More, actually.
Nearly 16,000 feet.

32:06.920 --> 32:08.480
-Really?
-Why?

32:08.560 --> 32:10.520
Condors. They're in the sky.

32:10.600 --> 32:11.920
Yes, but they fly
above the ground.

32:12.000 --> 32:14.680
Yes, I know, but in order to
catch up to them,
we must go high.

32:14.760 --> 32:17.640
You can't catch up with them
and just, just photograph
them in the face.

32:17.720 --> 32:20.880
I'm telling you, you want a
condor, we've gotta go high.

32:20.960 --> 32:22.680
Oh, my God.

32:22.760 --> 32:24.640
-What?
-I've seen it as well.

32:24.720 --> 32:26.000
What, my roof?

32:26.080 --> 32:28.120
That the only piece of fabric
you could find
to make a roof?

32:28.200 --> 32:30.400
-What is that?
-It's wild life.

32:30.480 --> 32:32.320
That's for a nursery
or something, isn't it?

32:32.400 --> 32:33.560
-I mean...
-Mate!

32:33.640 --> 32:35.160
It'll keep the sun
and rain off my head.

32:35.240 --> 32:37.080
-The rain?
-Well, it'll keep
the sun off.

32:37.160 --> 32:39.560
It's a really nice
installation. That is
a quality job as well.

32:39.640 --> 32:41.440
You've really...
that is crap.

32:41.520 --> 32:43.840
So I've got oxygen
for the altitude

32:43.920 --> 32:45.720
-which we're going to.
-Yeah.

32:45.800 --> 32:48.160
-That'll stop my face
disintegrating.
-It won't.

32:48.240 --> 32:52.480
-And that means
I can photograph birds.
-It won't.

32:52.560 --> 32:56.960
JEREMY: As it was
another 200-mile drive
to reach condor country,

32:57.040 --> 33:00.680
we decided to
get cracking immediately.

